name: Fire OG
body:
*Indica*
[ OG Kush x SFV OG Kush ]

One of the strongest OG Kush variants. The scent is similar to a cleaning astringent and can hit the head immediately after consumption. Its high THC content can cause an intense high that should be mediated for patients with lower tolerance. An immense euphoria adding to the creative buzz felt during an OG Kush medication can be very enjoyable to many users. Pain relief is not absent due to its OG parents but will not markedly induce any drowsiness. Those suffering from digestion problems to those needing mood elevations will all find much use for Fire OG Kush

name: Hindu Kush
body: Named for the mountainous region in the countries of Pakistan and Afghanistan comes the namesake for this strain, known as a lighter Indica. For having a mellow medication, this is a night time/pain relief patient's ideal choice.

name: Platinum Grape Ape
body:
[ Afghani x Skunk #1 x NL ]

A hybrid but some may grow to complete Indica in the current generation. However due to the potency, an initial head buzz is always felt before the typical Grape Ape effects. It becomes apparent once the sedative effects arise that pain relief, appetite stimulation and mood elevation are well on their way. The smoke is thick and heavy and provides the user with a fruity flavor which always compliments the strain after proper curing. 

This particular Grape Ape is mixed with some NL or possible Master Kush for its platinum genetics providing a higher THC percentage. Its low sativa characteristics provide comfort for those needing to be wary of anxiety-prone or drowsy effects.

name: Girl Scout Cookies
body:
[ Durban F1 X OG Kush X Cherry Pie Kush ]

This generation's Blue Dream in terms of popularity and medicinal effects. With fruity overtones, the undertones of Durban and OG Kush really come out during a smoke session revealing the earthy, piney flavors coming altogether for one of the finest strains to hit the Bay Area in previous years.

The effects can be felt all over from pain relief to euphoria, to a focused, functional high. Girl Scout Cookies come from a vast spectrum of Sativa to Indica lineage providing a mass audience with an enjoyable medication, from relaxing to adventuring. Great for night and day use.

name: Raspberry G.S.C.
body:
[ Cherry Kush x Durban Poison x OG Kush ]

With the genetics traditional to most Girl Scout Cookies, this resembles its lineage in effect, however the flavor of this cross with slightly more Cherry Kush changes its aroma and adds a newer experience to the beloved Bay Area strain. Slightly more indica than the usual GSC, this version is great for night time pain relief and can be a sleep aid. Those using during day time should be aware of its marked drowsy symptoms regardless of the immense uplifting, euphoric medication high.

name: Purple Kush
body:
[ Hindu Kush x Purple Afghani ]

The berry aroma is synonymous with purple strains so this one will carry the typical Indica attributes most patients needing pain relief and some insomnia relief with an enjoyable medication session. Its high THC content will be slightly overbearing to those of lower tolerance adding to a cerebral buzz, but for consistent smokers the usual pain relief aspects will shine through. Stress relief is just as strong but not uplifting enough to ever consider during day time use. Appetite stimulation will be prevalent so a low dose could be considered if needed without reducing a patients focus and functionality.

name: Bubba Kush
body:
[ Bubble Gum x Kush ]

An almost complete indica, the effects will immediately add to a couch-locking intensity. The pain relief attributes are exceptional and patients of all types can enjoy its benefits without added drowsiness or anxiety, providing a balanced stress reliever.

name: OG Kush (Greenhouse)
body:
[ Chemdawg x Hindu Kush ]

A world renowned strain, with genetics of Afghani plants and now cross-grown with sativas in California to provide a newer uplifting effect while preserving its original, distinct flavor and ultimate pain relief attributes. The fuel and citrus taste mimic the initial cerebral hit you feel on first ingestion and the earthy after taste is a good mirror for its buzzing ability to create a body lock without losing focus or function, providing a great ratio of head to body for medication.

name: G.D.P.
body:
[ Big Bud x Urkle ]

One of the world's most recognized Indica signature strains. Granddaddy Purple is a classic euphoric, pain relieving enjoyable medication that exhibits just enough cerebral buzz to prevent drowsiness and maintain mood relaxation. Its sweet, grape flavor is ideal for smoking but many users still experience the same herbal satisfaction when vaporizing or consuming it through food.

name: Purple Flow
body:
[ Purple Thai x Afghani ]

Flo, an award winning strain for almost 20 years, this variation has slightly more purple to it. The indica aspect of this plant can contain a higher CBD percentage, aiding much more to pain relief than other purple strains lacking CBD and compensating with THC sedative effects. The piney, skunky flavor is much different when smoked, causing a surprise cerebral buzz followed by the typical indica feeling of euphoria in a body high without too much marked drowsiness.

name: Sweet Island Skunk
body:
[ Northern Lights x Haze x Sweet Pink Grapefruit ]

Roughly a 70/30 Sativa dominant hybrid, the effects in this strain are almost always felt in the head but can aid to numerous body ailments. From elevating mood, appetite stimulation, migraine and arthritis relief, this is an ideal medication for all day use for those wanting to avoid a heavy body high but still requiring the pain management. Earthy-sweet undertones can provide an enjoyable smoke session that can be as memorable as the effects felt after the initial cloudy head buzz.

name: Jack Herer
body:
[ Northern Lights x Shiva Skunk x Haze ]

Named for a legendary Cannabis activist who dedicated his life to the exposure of the plant as medicine, this strain is one of the most recognized in the world. The taste is very distinct and many can recognize it on first inhalation. Its lineage has maintained a reputable flavor paired with its effect that has persevered through years of growth.

An intense psychoactive high that must be taken lightly if a user is prone to anxiety or higher THC levels. No pain relief or night time benefits are contained in Jack so one should restrict it to just day time usage.

name: Candy Jack
body:
[ Cotton Candy x Jack Herer ]

With the fruity overtone, and astringent/peppery undertones, this strain can be remarked as one of the best day time medications. 

A splendid sativa experience providing many benefits to those needing aid for stress, anxiety, depression and various mood disorders. The cerebral effect will be ideal for those with a higher tolerance though, due to this strains tendency of high potency.

name: Dutch Treat
body:
[ Northern Lights x Skunk x Haze ]

A sativa dominant hybrid with an enjoyable pine/citrus aroma and flavor. Patients with higher tolerances can enjoy this just as much with less medication due to its high THC potency. A psychoactive effect that brings the user into an ultimate state of bliss while also providing benefit for some mild pain relief.

name: Agent Orange
body:
[ Orange Velvet x Jack the Ripper ]

A sativa with numerous uplifting attributes remembered for its distinct citrus taste.
Due to its lineage tracing into Jack strains as well as Space Queen, the effects will be almost completely cerebral. A perfect day time medication for those looking to remain clear-minded and alert.

name: New York Diesel
body: New York Haze x Sour Diesel

name: Sour Diesel
body:
[ Chemdawg x Super Skunk x Northern Lights ]

One of the world's most popular strains, the name speaks of its nature as a plant and medicine. The aroma/flavor is just like it states, Diesel. It's pungent namesake provides the user with the self explanatory hint that it hits you like fuel. Alert and focused, many will enjoy its use in the day time for aiding in creativity, stress-relief, and mood elevation. Suggested for patients with disorders ranging from Bipolar to ADD/ADHD to PTSD, this strain has an intense THC percentage that should be taken lightly unless the person has a higher tolerance.

name: Chemdawg
body:
[ OG Kush x Sour Diesel ]

A mostly sativa dominant hybrid. An intense euphoric head high that does not remain absent from entering the body as well. Some patients with lower tolerance may want to stray from the effects of Chem Dawg, the rumored grandparent of popular strains such as OG Kush and Sour Diesel. It is a recommended agent for aid of stress and depression, providing instant relief after ingestion.

name: Harlequin
body:
[ Colombian Gold x Laos/Swiss landrace strains x Nepalese Indica ] 

This strain is sought after highly in the medical community in regards to its high CBD content. With levels up to 10x that of an Indica plant, many users needing pain relief for chemotherapy, MS or various chronic pains can find benefit here. Resembling a ruderalis plant in effects, the flavor is much better due to the diversity of lineage in this strain. Not much psychoactive effect is applied during medication of Harlequin but it is almost easily ignored with the interesting body buzz felt after smoking or consuming it. Ideal for stress and pain relief without any noticeable side effects.

name: Pineapple Kush
body:
[Pineapple x Master Kush]

This hybrid strain is quite exquisite for flavor connoisseurs. Fruit based but butter complimented have been several comments during the strain's existence. Coming from two differently genetic parents, this hybrid strain will benefit patients of all types. The strain induces euphoria benefiting those with anxiety or depression and various mood disorders while alleviating mild pains from arthritis or migraines.

name: SeaTrain
body: High CBD strain, locally grown in the Bay Area. Little is known as it is a newer distinct hybrid with a heavy body feel that could be ideal vaporized for flavor and effect of medication.

name: Chocolate Kush
body:
[ Chocolope x Kosher Kush ]

An indica dominant hybrid. Award winning and recognized in the cannabis industry due to the success of its parent, Chocolope. The color is much like its scent which some have stated may resemble an earthy dessert.

The effects are still heady but mostly a short cerebral buzz followed by a couch-locking heaviness. It will provide excellent pain relief, especially for patients with HIV/AIDS, cancer and may even aid with fibromyalgia, migraines or arthritis.

name: Humboldt HoneyDew
body: An area of the namesake town Humboldt, Honeydew is a district comprising of wetter, coastal temperatures adding to the unique growth of this strain. Regarded as a Kush by locals, its genetics are mostly unknown currently due to its numerous crosses in one of the largest cannabis growing communities in the world. It is heavy yielding and has a spicy smell/flavor added to its earthy tones so users searching a balanced hybrid can expect euphoria along with mild pain relief.
